<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS -
        INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the engine in the vertical position, lubricate the camshaft and the camshaft
                    bushings using clean engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently slide camshaft assembly into crankcase. Be careful not to damage camshaft
                    bushings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align camshaft gear so bolts can be inserted through gear access holes into thrust
                    plate. Tighten each bolt to special torque value. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_100.xml" xrefid="ef1050529">5.29</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install idler gears as described in Section 8
                    <hotlnk document="e105_E10508.xml" xrefid="e10508">"TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER"</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align gear train timing marks. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_88.xml" xrefid="ef1050518">5.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check camshaft gear backlash and camshaft end play as described in Section 8
                    <hotlnk document="e105_E10508.xml" xrefid="e10508">"TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER"</hotlnk>.
                    Specifications must be met.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
